snippet.textDisplay: 25 years old man betting 37 years old man. And don't lie to yourself Cowboy is old man. Lost 3 in a row. It was free win for Conor set up by Dana. Like most of his carrier. When real fights came Conor crumbles. And it's not like if didn't we didn't see it already. When fight is real. When it's not a 40 sec beat down. Conor quits. Conor is mentally weak and can't deal with adversity. When things are going his way he is on top of the world when things are not going he was he is way down in the gutter and has no idea how to get out. That's not a fighters mentality. Fighting is about overcoming adversity.  And that's something i think Conor can't learn. He would until now if he could. It's easy to be a fighter when you are one raining down punches. Hard to be one when you are the one taking them. And if you think Conor will beat Tony or Khabib or Usman or Woodley in 40 seconds. That's just ridicules. Man who punches old people from behind doesn't have enough self control to engage in 25 minutes war. Cause after 20 minutes when you are sitting in that chair when your lungs are burning.
